
[1]amendment

   AMEND'MENT, n.

   1. An alteration or change for the better; correction of a fault or
   faults; reformation of life, by quitting vices.

   2. A word, clause or paragraph, added or proposed to be added to a bill
   before a legislature.

   3. In law, the correction of an error in a writ or process.

   Shakespeare uses it for the recovery of health, but this sense is
   unusual.
